mpati score is a pictorial tool used to predict difficult preoperative laryngoscopy and intubation, as well as being widely used as a routine screen before procedural sedation.\u00a0\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt is important to note that it cannot be evaluated in young children and in patients who cannot cooperate due to their medical condition.\u00a0\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGrade I: soft palate, uvula, fauces, pillars visible.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGrade II: soft palate, major part of uvula, fauces visible.\u00a0\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGrade III\u003C/strong\u003E: soft palate, base of uvula visible (correct).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGrade IV: only hard palate visible.\u00a0\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGrade V does not exist.\u00a0\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The Mallampati score is a predictor of ease or difficulty of laryngoscopy and intubation."],"references":["Green SM, Roback MG. Is the Mallampati Score Useful for Emergency\u00a0Department Airway Management or\u00a0Procedural Sedation? Ann Emerg Med. 2019 Aug;74(2):251-259. doi: 10.1016/j.annemergmed.2018.12.021. Epub 2019 Feb 16. PMID: 30782435."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"24048"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"801"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"15891"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"15891","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/15891"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/600eb1a9-33b8-44d9-bfff-0d60f4344531.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/600eb1a9-33b8-44d9-bfff-0d60f4344531.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":508,"height":600}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"24048","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/24048"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-09-26T20:23:03+09:30","updatedAt":"2023-09-26T20:23:03+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id